Authorities says a group of about 10 men took congregants belongings including jewellery and cash. JOHANNESBURG - Police are appealing to the public to assist in a search for a group of about 10 men who robbed a church in Alexandra, leaving congregants in shock. Authoritiessays the congregation was gathered for Friday night prayers, when theburglars ordered them to lie down and took theirbelongings includingrings, watches, handbags and cash. Police says the suspects fled with a VW Polo. Police spokesperson Kay Makhubela says no one has been arrested and they have opened a case of business robbery among others. On their way out, they shot a priest but he was not injured, the bullet on teared his trousers. A case of attempted murder was included in the case and our investigation continue.